Query True when Typical use <code>get_key(key)</code> the key is held continuous movement or charging <code>get_key_down(key)</code> the key changed to pressed this frame jump, open, confirm <code>get_key_up(key)</code> the key changed to released this frame release, stop charging <p>The same distinction exists for mouse buttons. A <code>down</code> or <code>up</code> query is an edge event: read it in normal frame updates, not as a persistent state.</p> <pre><code>from Infernux import InxComponent, Vector3
from Infernux.input import Input, KeyCode


class KeyboardMover(InxComponent):
    speed: float = 4.0

    def update(self, delta_time: float) -&gt; None:
        direction = 0.0
        if Input.get_key(KeyCode.A):
            direction -= 1.0
        if Input.get_key(KeyCode.D):
            direction += 1.0

        self.transform.translate(Vector3(direction * self.speed * delta_time, 0.0, 0.0))
</code></pre> <p>Multiplying by <code>delta_time</code> converts a per-second speed into the distance for this frame.</p>

